Project Requirements

Project Name (Working): Interactive Animated AI Companions for Children

1. Target Users

Children aged 4–10 years

Parents / Guardians (control & monitoring)

Admin / Content managers

2. Functional Requirements
2.1 User Interaction

The system shall allow children to interact with animated characters (Crow, Turtle, Cow).

The system shall support input via:

Voice (primary)

Text or button-based options (fallback)

The system shall respond in real-time with audio, animation, and facial reactions.

2.2 Animated Characters

The system shall include multiple animated characters, each with:

Unique personality

Distinct voice

Custom reactions

The system shall support facial expressions, including:

Happy

Laughing

Thinking

Confused

Surprised

The system shall trigger animations based on conversation context.

2.3 Conversation & AI Logic

The system shall generate child-safe AI responses.

The system shall adapt replies based on:

Child’s answer

Emotional tone

Conversation history

The system shall ask follow-up questions to maintain engagement.

The system shall support storytelling, jokes, and simple quizzes.

2.4 Emotion Detection & Reaction

The system shall analyze child responses to detect:

Happiness

Confusion

Excitement

Silence / hesitation

The system shall map emotions to facial and voice reactions.

The system shall adjust humor and difficulty level accordingly.

2.5 Voice System

The system shall convert speech to text accurately for children’s voices.

The system shall generate expressive text-to-speech output.

The system shall support different voice styles per character.

2.6 Learning & Engagement

The system shall include educational elements, such as:

Vocabulary building

Simple math

Moral stories

The system shall reward engagement using:

Stickers

Sounds

Unlockable animations

2.7 Parental Controls

The system shall provide a parent dashboard.

Parents shall be able to:

Set daily usage limits

View interaction summaries

Enable / disable voice input

The system shall prevent collection of personal information.

2.8 Safety & Moderation

The system shall filter inappropriate content.

The system shall block unsafe or unknown topics.

The system shall provide safe fallback responses when unsure.

The system shall comply with child-safety regulations (COPPA / GDPR-K).

2.9 Admin Panel

Admin users shall manage:

Characters

Dialog templates

Learning content

Difficulty levels

The system shall allow updating content without app redeployment.

3. Non-Functional Requirements
3.1 Performance

Response time shall be under 2 seconds.

Animations shall play smoothly (30–60 FPS).

3.2 Scalability

The system shall support thousands of concurrent users.

Backend shall be cloud-scalable.

3.3 Availability & Reliability

System uptime shall be ≥ 99.5%.

Automatic recovery from failures.

3.4 Security

Data shall be encrypted in transit and at rest.

No child voice recordings stored permanently.

Secure authentication for parents and admins.

3.5 Usability

Interface shall be simple and colorful.

Minimal reading required.

Large buttons and clear audio.

3.6 Accessibility

Subtitles for audio responses.

Color-blind friendly UI.

Adjustable speech speed.

4. Technical Requirements
4.1 Frontend

Game-like UI (Web / Mobile / Tablet)

Animation engine (2D or 3D)

Microphone access

4.2 Backend

API-based architecture

Conversation state management

AI integration layer

4.3 AI & ML

Child-safe LLM

Emotion classification model

Rule-based safety guardrails

4.4 Database

User profiles (non-personal)

Interaction logs (anonymous)

Rewards & progress tracking

5. Integration Requirements

Speech-to-Text API

Text-to-Speech API

AI language model

Animation trigger engine

6. Constraints & Assumptions

Requires internet connection

Designed for touch devices

Age-appropriate content only

7. Future Enhancements

More characters (Lion, Monkey, Robot)

Multiplayer story mode

AR characters

Offline limited mode

8. Success Criteria

Average session time > 10 minutes

High child engagement rate

Positive parent feedback

Zero safety incidents
